{"type":"message","id":"960a02e0","parentId":"aaa744ef","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:47:53.009Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r7qn6rz1dt2g_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5086\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='the' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 094715 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement the classifier on existing pulse logs to measure invariant/variant accuracy against the >70% success criterion.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"brisk-summit","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5086\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='' file='' new_len=0\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation parse failed] old='' file='the' new_len=0\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 094715 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement the classifier on existing pulse logs to measure invariant/variant accuracy against the >70% success criterion.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360073006}}
{"type":"message","id":"b35cc5b5","parentId":"960a02e0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:47:53.013Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_r7qn6rz1dt2g_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094616\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nThe session has established:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. A major insight has emerged: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n3. Next action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete next step. Let me look at what files exist to understand the structure better, and create a TIC experiment implementation.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Look at the log files to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC experiment script or module\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory and the research directory to understand the structure, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority - implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment implementation that analyzes pulse logs to classify content as temporally invariant or variant, then uses invariants to predict subsequent pulse content. This tests the core hypothesis that compression IS causal discovery.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY Validation\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis:** Causal structure = Invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n**Success Criteria:**\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy from invariants\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n\r\n### Phase 1: Extract Pulse Features\r\nFor each pulse log, extract:\r\n1. **File operations** - what files were modified, when, how\r\n2. **Goal state** - current goals, pending items, completion status\r\n3. **Architectural decisions** - insights, synthesis notes\r\n4. **Action patterns** - mutation types, scope of changes\r\n\r\n### Phase 2: Classify Invariants vs Variants\r\n**Invariants** (stable across pulses):\r\n- Core architecture principles (e.g., \"Breakaway is stateless\")\r\n- File structure conventions\r\n- Goal hierarchy\r\n- Script mechanics\r\n\r\n**Variants** (change per pulse):\r\n- Specific content of edits\r\n- Detailed findings\r\n- Implementation details\r\n- Timestamps, session IDs\r\n\r\n### Phase 3: Predict Next Pulse\r\nGiven invariants from pulse N, predict:\r\n1. What goals will persist\r\n2. What files will be touched\r\n3. What architectural insights will carry forward\r\n4. What will be new/variant\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```powershell\r\n# TIC Classifier for Pulse Logs\r\n# Analyzes patterns across pulse_*.md files\r\n\r\n$logDir = \"logs\"\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem $logDir/pulse_*.md | Sort-Object Name\r\n\r\n# Feature extraction for each pulse\r\n$features = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    $pulseFeatures = @{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        HasGoalState = $content -match \"## (Active|Completed|Pending)\"\r\n        HasMutation = $content -match \"### MUTATION\"\r\n        HasObservation = $content -match \"### OBSERVATION\"\r\n        FileReferences = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?<=file:\\s)[^\\s]+')\r\n        InsightCount = ([regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(insight|hypothesis|synthesis)') ).Count\r\n        ArchitectureTerms = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(architecture|invariant|variant|compression|causal)')\r\n        ActionVerbs = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(create|modify|analyze|compare|synthesize)')\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $features += $pulseFeatures\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify each feature as INVARIANT or VARIANT\r\n$invariantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\",\r\n    \"gaps?.*compress\",\r\n    \"phase \\d\",\r\n    \"pulse.*script\",\r\n    \"goal\",\r\n    \"architecture\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$variantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\",\r\n    \"pulse_\\d{8}\",\r\n    \"specific.*content\",\r\n    \"concrete.*action\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Output classification results\r\n$results = @{\r\n    Invariants = @()\r\n    Variants = @()\r\n    Predictions = @()\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants (appear in >60% of pulses)\r\n$allContent = ($pulseFiles | ForEach-Object { Get-Content $_.FullName -Raw }) -join \" \"\r\n\r\nforeach ($pattern in $invariantPatterns) {\r\n    $matches = [regex]::Matches($allContent, $pattern)\r\n    if ($matches.Count / $pulseFiles.Count -gt 0.6) {\r\n        $results.Invariants += $pattern\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify variants (appear in <40% of pulses)\r\nforeach ($pattern in $variantPatterns) {\r\n    $matches = [regex]::Matches($allContent, $pattern)\r\n    if ($matches.Count / $pulseFiles.Count -lt 0.4) {\r\n        $results.Variants += $pattern\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Prediction: invariants from pulse N predict structure of pulse N+1\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulseFiles.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $current = Get-Content $pulseFiles[$i].FullName -Raw\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:46:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360073009}}
